      "company_match": "Polaris",
      "author_email": "raouf@gazaskygeeks.com",
      "body": "The company was established in 2023. It was previously known as Synergy before the business was split. \nThe company specializes in digital transformation solutions for both: \nEnterprise sector \nSME sector \nThey offer no-code solutions as part of their service portfolio. \nThey also provide ERP solutions for SMEs, especially for factories, and they are a SAP partner in ERP-related services. \nSome of their clients include: \nNational Bank \nAziza \nCartoon Factory \nFurniture factories/companies \nDuring the war, the company tried to shift its focus more toward products rather than services. \nCurrently, they have 4 products, including: \nBig Data product in collaboration with Ooredoo \nSmall ERP solution under a SaaS model \nThe current team consists of 13 employees, based in Nablus and Ramallah, and most of them are working remotely due to the situation. \nThe company is looking to expand its team. \nTheir main support needs from GSG include: \nUpskilling \nTrain-to-Hire (TTH) \nMarketing & Branding \nThe company is currently trying to register in Jordan. \nThey are also interested in expanding to the Saudi market, but they face difficulties because they are a Palestinian company. As a result, they are currently considering working through a partner in KSA. \nThey are interested in receiving advisory support on proposal writing for the KSA market. \nThey previously had a bad experience with registration attempts in KSA, which did not work out, so they are now focusing more on Jordan instead. \nThe main products they want to focus on for the KSA market are: \nBig Data product \nERP SaaS product \nThey are interested in working with Elevate Bridge, especially after identifying which product is best suited for which market. \nPriority areas: \nMarket Access \nLegal registration \nTrain-to-Hire (TTH) \nFor TTH, they are initially considering 3 resources, with a 100% hiring ratio, in areas such as: \nBusiness and accounting \nMechanical engineering \nThe expected salary range is around 800 USD. \nThey are currently waiting for confirmation from Iraq-based clients, and they will send a follow-up email later to confirm: ",
